          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is tender, scoop the <strong>softened aubergine flesh</strong> out of the skins with a spoon, pulling it apart as you go – this is your <strong>pulled aubergine</strong></p><p>Tip: Carefully hold the stalks (they will be hot!) to scrape the flesh out easily, then discard the skins and reserve the tray[s]!</p><p>Once the onion has started to soften, add the <strong>pulled aubergine</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>soy sauce </strong>to the pan and cook for 2 min until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1684229764117-x200.jpg",
